<subsection xml:id="subsec-construction-of-a-circle-touching-the-sides-of-a-triangle">
        <title>Construction of a Circle Touching the Sides of a Triangle</title>
        <p>
            A circle touching the sides (faces) of a triangle is called an <term>incircle.</term>
        </p>
        <activity>
        <p>
            Construct an incircle for the given triangle. Follow the instructions below. 
        </p>
        <p>
           <term>Instructions</term> 
        </p>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select the <term>angle bisector tool (Window 4)</term> and click on the points <m>B,\, A,\, C</m> to bisect the angle <m>BAC</m>
                        Then click points <m>B,\, C,\, A\,</m> to bisect the angle <m>BCA.</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select <term>intersect tool (Window 2)</term> and mark the point of intersection <m>D,</m> of the two angle bisectors lines.
                         Then click on another point of intersection <m>E</m> of the angle bisector with either segment <m>BC</m> or <m>AB</m>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Select <term>circle with center tool (Window 3)</term> and click at points <m>D</m> and  <m>E</m> to construct the circle.
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>

        <figure>
            <caption>Incircle</caption>
            <interactive xml:id="geogebra-incircle" platform="geogebra" width="95%" aspect="4:3">
            <slate xml:id="incircle" surface="geogebra" material="xbweuvvu" aspect="4:3">
                enableShiftDragZoom(true);
                showResetIcon(true);
            </slate>
            </interactive>
        </figure>
        </activity>
    </subsection>